4907:     /**
4908:      * Called by {@link android.view.View#requestLayout()} if the view hierarchy is currently
4909:      * undergoing a layout pass. requestLayout() should not generally be called during layout,
4910:      * unless the container hierarchy knows what it is doing (i.e., it is fine as long as
4911:      * all children in that container hierarchy are measured and laid out at the end of the layout
4912:      * pass for that container). If requestLayout() is called anyway, we handle it correctly
4913:      * by registering all requesters during a frame as it proceeds. At the end of the frame,
4914:      * we check all of those views to see if any still have pending layout requests, which
4915:      * indicates that they were not correctly handled by their container hierarchy. If that is
4916:      * the case, we clear all such flags in the tree, to remove the buggy flag state that leads
4917:      * to blank containers, and force a second request/measure/layout pass in this frame. If
4918:      * more requestLayout() calls are received during that second layout pass, we post those
4919:      * requests to the next frame to avoid possible infinite loops.
4920:      *
4921:      * <p>The return value from this method indicates whether the request should proceed
4922:      * (if it is a request during the first layout pass) or should be skipped and posted to the
4923:      * next frame (if it is a request during the second layout pass).</p>
4924:      *
4925:      * @param view the view that requested the layout.
4926:      *
4927:      * @return true if request should proceed, false otherwise.
4928:      */
4929:     boolean requestLayoutDuringLayout(final View view) {
4930:         if (view.mParent == null || view.mAttachInfo == null) {
4931:             // Would not normally trigger another layout, so just let it pass through as usual
4932:             return true;
4933:         }
4934:         if (!mLayoutRequesters.contains(view)) {
4935:             mLayoutRequesters.add(view);
4936:         }
4937:         if (!mHandlingLayoutInLayoutRequest) {
4938:             // Let the request proceed normally; it will be processed in a second layout pass
4939:             // if necessary
4940:             return true;
4941:         } else {
4942:             // Don't let the request proceed during the second layout pass.
4943:             // It will post to the next frame instead.
4944:             return false;
4945:         }
4946:     }
